A. E. BURNETT, District Director of Immigration for Los Angeles District, District No. 31, Appellant, v. YEE GOOK HOR, Appellee. No. 7257. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 21, 1933. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Ignatius F. Parker, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. J. E. Keating and T. E. Bowen, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for the respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
